The executive director (Technical), Niger Delta Power Holding Company (NDPHC), Engr Ife Oyedele, has said that Ondo State is endowed with enormous potentials for the betterment of its people but for the maladministration it suffered in recent times. Oyedele, who stated this during an interaction with journalists in Abuja, yesterday, added that mismanagement of Ondo resources has been the bane of development. “The mismanagement of the enormous resources of the state by its administrators has left the Sunshine State with impoverishment and not too satisfactory federal presence and projects, at least in the last four years”. “More than before, Ondo state is in dire need of someone that can attract life impacting projects to the State. It is unfortunate that despite the availability of mineral resources such as Bitumen and Crude Oil in the state, that the level of poverty is still high in the state owing to bad governance by the present rulers”. “Its unfortunate that government businesses have been taken over as family affairs in the state as developmental projects are not feasible across the state in the last four years”. “Let me use this opportunity to call on the citizens and good people of Ondo State as a man of honesty, humility, integrity and philanthropy, that they deserve better than what they have today”. “It is sad that the rate of unemployment and youth restiveness in the state is worrisome and could only be arrested if the right candidate clinch the governorship ticket of the ruling All Progressives Party (APC) in the next election,” Oyedele said. He therefore called on the state’s political class to use the opportunity of the forthcoming governorship election in the state to choose a passionate man of integrity who has empathy for the people and understands the challenges of a modern state like Ondo.